==Miss Veronica==

{{Main|Veronica}}

'''Miss Veronica''' (born December 16, 1991 in Olongapo City, [[Philippines]]), currently named '''Veronica_Vacuous'' and also known as '''Miss V''' is an American socialite, entertainer, entrepreneur, diva, It-Girl, icon, and queen bee and upcoming actress, singer/songwriter and fashion designer. Notoriously charming and beautiful, Veronica was raised in an affluent, conservative city in Olongapo City, Philippines but moved to Southern California (lived in both [[Orange County]] and [[Los Angeles]]) when she was 7 and became a social butterfly. She currently lives in Los Angeles and runs it. When Veronica was merely 14, stumbled into the [[IMDb]] scene (both The Soapbox and the Sandbox) and immediately become a household name, which she became known for her controversial, funny and energetic personality. From making up her own calculated vocabulary to her dramatic clashes and outrageous outbursts towards other members. Her broad personality covering many different dimensions along with her opinionated ways made a lot of Soapboxers love to hate and hate to love her (known as ''haters''), but Veronica is Veronica and nobody can take that away. Veronica has been described by friends as quirky, witty and extremely spontaneous, an easy person to get to know, and as well as a great and true friend once she lets you inside. She is the epitome of classy, but don't mess with her, because she will drop her Louis Vuitton and will snatch a bitch.  She embodies strength, pride and determination while being fierce, fabulous and flawless at the same time. She's the only Miss America. She's what your mother was supposed to be. She's perfect.

She is also a great role model for the younger audience. ''“If you want your girls to feel strong and intelligent and be outspoken and fight for what they think is right, then I want to be that type of role model.” – Queen Veronica''

Miss Veronica answers fan mails and questions on her official [[Formspring]]. [http://www.formspring.me/missveronicaaa]

